The Weekly UAS7 assessment is a 7-day diary record, including 7 subscales as follows:
-HSS7, a 7-point scale ranging from 0 to 6 where 0=no hives, 1=mild hives, 2=hives on 1-2 limbs, 3=hives in ≥3 areas of body and/or on most days, 4=hives in ≥2 areas of face; 5=hives on most days, 6= severe hives at midpoint, 7=widespread hives (covermost of body) and severe (at midpoint);
-ISS7, a 7-point scale ranging from 0 to 6 where 0=no itch, 1=mild itch, 2= itch on 1-2 locations, 3=in ≥2 locations, 4=itch on most days, 5=itch on most days, 6= severe itch at midpoint (or severe and uninterrupted), 7=severe itch throughout;
- UAS7, the mean of HSS7 and ISS7, ranging from 0 to 28 where 0=no hives, 1=mild hives, 2=hives on 1-2 limbs, 3=hives in ≥2 areas and/or most days, 4-5=hives in ≥3 areas and severe at least at mid-point, 6=severe hives and uninterrupted 7=severe throughout;
Remember that these outcomes are scored from 0-7, with 0=no urticaria and 7=severe urticaria and severe itch. 
